steps.title: Welcome to Moodle 4!
steps.content: This brief tour will show you the new features in your dashboard.

steps.title: Alert section
steps.content:
At the top of your dashboard, there is an Alert section that keeps you informed about important updates, changes, or issues related to the Moodle platform. 

Alerts will only show when there is an important announcement. If you can't see the Alerts section, it looks like the image below.

steps.title: Pick up where you left off
steps.content: The new "Pick up where you left off” feature allows you to conveniently resume your learning from the point you last accessed. It helps you quickly pick up where you left off in your courses and activities, making it easier to continue your progress.

steps.title: My courses
steps.content:
Use the "My Courses" navigation tab the "View all your courses" in the 'Pick up where you left off' block, to view all of the courses that you are enrolled in.

There, you can choose to show courses currently in progress, in the past or the future, or courses which you have starred.

steps.title: Timeline
steps.content: The Timeline feature provides a visual representation of your upcoming Moodle activities and their deadlines in chronological order. It assists you in managing your tasks efficiently by offering a clear overview of important dates and ensuring you stay on top of your due dates.

steps.title: Feedback block
steps.content:
The Feedback feature centralises all your assignments’ feedback and aims to streamline the process of accessing and reviewing feedback, enhancing your assessment experience.

The Feedback feature will only show if you have feedback from a Moodle or Turnitin assignment, so you might not see it at first. The image below shows what it will look like.

steps.title: News
steps.content: The News feature shows you topical UCL events and information.

steps.title: Thank you!
steps.content:
These are the key navigation changes to the Moodle dashboard. We hope these changes improve your learning experience.

Thank you.
